obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12590)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12590&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Commission of Sati`
  line `(Prevention) Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in a State on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different States.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21stMarch, 1988, vide notification No. G.S.R. 359(E), dated 21st March, 1988, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12591)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12591&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(b) "glorification", in relation to sati, whether such sati, was committed before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, includes, among other things,--`
  line
  line `(i) the observance of any ceremony or the taking out of a procession in connection with the`
  line `commission of sati; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the supporting, justifying or propagating the practice of sati in any manner; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the arranging of any function to eulogise the person who has committed sati; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the creation of a trust, or the collection of funds, or the construction of a temple or other`
  line `structure or the carrying on of any form of worship or the performance of any ceremony thereat,`
  line `with a view to perpetuate the honour of, or to preserve the memory of, a person who has`
  line `committed sati;`
  line
  line `(c) "sati" means the act of burning or burying alive of--`
  line
  line `(i) any widow along with the body of her deceased husband or any other relative or with any`
  line `article, object or thing associated with the husband or such relative; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any woman along with the body of any of her relatives, irrespective of whether such`
  line `burning or burying is claimed to be voluntary on the part of the widow or the woman or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(d) "Special Court" means a Special Court constituted under section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) "temple" includes any building or other structure, whether roofed or not, constructed or made`
  line `to preserve the memory of a person in respect of whom sati has been committed or used or intended`
  line `to be used for the carrying on of any form of worship or for the observance of any ceremony in`
  line `connection with such commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Indian Penal Code (45`
  line `of 1860), or in the Code shall have the same meanings as are respectively assigned to them in the Indian`
  line `Penal Code or the Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12592)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Attempt to commit sati.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12592&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Penal Code(45 of`
  line `1860), whoever attempts to commit sati and does any act towards such commission shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Special Court trying an offence under this section shall, before convicting any`
  line `person, take into consideration the circumstances leading to the commission of the offence, the act`
  line `committed, the state or mind of the person charged of the offence at the time of the commission of the act`
  line `and all other relevant factors.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12593)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Abetment of sati.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12593&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860),`
  line `if any person commits sati, whoever abets the commission of such sati, either directly or indirectly, shall`
  line `be punishable with death or imprisonment for life and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person attempts to commit sati, whoever abets such attempt, either directly or indirectly,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for life and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, any of the following acts or the like shall also be`
  line `deemed to be an abetment, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any inducement to a widow or woman to get her burnt or buried alive along with the body of`
  line `her deceased husband or with any other relative or with any article, object or thing associated with the`
  line `husband or such relative, irrespective of whether she is in a fit state of mind or is labouring under a`
  line `state of intoxication or stupefaction or other cause impeding the exercise of her free will;`
  line
  line `(b) making a widow or woman believe that the commission of sati would result in some spiritual`
  line `benefit to her or her deceased husband or relative or the general well being of the family;`
  line
  line `(c) encouraging a widow or woman to remain fixed in her resolve to commit sati and thus`
  line `instigating her to commit sati;`
  line
  line `(d) participating in any procession in connection with the commission of sati or aiding the widow`
  line `or woman in her decision to commit sati by taking her along with body of her deceased husband or`
  line `relation to the cremation or burial ground;`
  line
  line `(e) being present at the place where sati is committed as an active participant to such commission`
  line `or to any ceremony connected with it;`
  line
  line `(f) preventing or obstructing the widow or woman from saving herself from being burnt or buried`
  line alive;
  line
  line `(g) obstructing, or interfering with, the police in the discharge of its duties of taking any steps to`
  line `prevent the commission of sati.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12594)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Punishment for glorification of sati.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12594&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does any act for the glorification of sati shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to`
  line `seven years and with fine which shall not be less than five thousand rupees but which may extend to thirty`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12595)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to prohibit certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12595&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Collector or the District Magistrate is of the`
  line `opinion that sati or any abetment thereof is being, or is about to be committed, he may, by order, prohibit`
  line `the doing of any act towards the commission of sati by any person in any area or areas specified in the`
  line order.
  line
  line `(2)The Collector or the District Magistrate may also, by order, prohibit the glorification in any`
  line `manner of sati by any person in any area or areas specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes any order made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall, if such`
  line `contravention is not punishable under any other provision of this Act, be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to seven years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than five thousand rupees but which may extend to thirty thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12596)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to remove certain temples or other structures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12596&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, if it is`
  line `satisfied that in any temple or other structure which has been in existence for not less than twenty years,`
  line `any form of worship or the performance of any ceremony is carried on with a view to perpetuate the`
  line `honour of, or to preserve the memory of, any person in respect of whom sati has been committed, by`
  line `order, direct the removal of such temple or other structure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector or the District Magistrate may, if he is satisfied that in any temple or other structure,`
  line `other than that referred to in sub-section (1), any form of worship or the performance of any ceremony is`
  line `carried on with a view to perpetuate the honour of, or to preserve the memory of, any person is respect of`
  line `whom sati has been committed, by order, direct the removal of such temple or other structure.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) is not complied with, the State`
  line `Government or the Collector or the District Magistrate, as the case may be, shall cause the temple or other`
  line `structure to be removed through a police officer not below the rank of a Sub-Inspector at the cost of the`
  line defaulter.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12597)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to seize certain properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12597&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Collector or the District Magistrate has reason`
  line `to believe that any funds or property have been collected or acquired for the purpose of glorification of`
  line `the commission of any sati or which may be found under circumstances which create suspicion of the`
  line `commission of any offence under this Act, he may seize such funds or property.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Collector or District Magistrate acting under sub-section (1) shall report the seizure to the`
  line `Special Court, if any, constituted to try any offence in relation to which such funds or property were`
  line `collected or acquired and shall await the orders of such Special Court as to the disposal of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12598)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Trial of offences under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12598&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, all`
  line `offences under this Act shall be triable only by a Special Court constituted under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute one or more Special`
  line `Courts for the trial of offences under this Act and every Special Court shall exercise jurisdiction in respect`
  line `of the whole or such part of the State as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) A Special Court shall be presided over by a Judge to be appointed by the State Government with`
  line `the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(4) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judge of a Special Court unless he is,`
  line `immediately before such appointment, a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions Judge in any State.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12599)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Special Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12599&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every Special Court, the State Government shall appoint a`
  line `person to be a Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be eligible to be appointed as a Special Public Prosecutor under this section only if`
  line `he had been in practice as an advocate for not less than seven years or has held any post for a period of`
  line `not less than seven years under the State requiring special knowledge of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person appointed as a Special Public Prosecutor under this section shall be deemed to be a`
  line `Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause (u) of section 2 of the Code and the provisions of the`
  line `Code shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12600)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure and powers of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12600&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Special Court may take cognizance of any`
  line `offence, without the accused being committed to it for trial, upon receiving a complaint of facts which`
  line `constitute such offence, or upon a police report of such facts.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, a Special Court shall, for the purpose of the trial of any`
  line `offence, have all the powers of a Court of Session and shall try such offence as if it were a Court of`
  line `Session, so far as may be, in accordance with the procedure prescribed in the Code for trial before a Court`
  line `of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12601)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Special Court with respect to other offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12601&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) When trying any offence under`
  line `this Act, a Special Court may also try any other offence with which the accused may, under the Code, be`
  line `charged at the same trial if the offence is connected with such other offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the course of any trial of any offence under this Act it is found that the accused person has`
  line `committed any other offence under this Act or under any other law, a Special Court may convict such`
  line `person also of such other offence and pass any sentence authorised by this Act or such other law for the`
  line `punishment thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) In every inquiry or trial, the proceedings shall be held as expeditiously as possible and, in`
  line `particular, where the examination of witnesses has begun, the same shall be continued from day to day`
  line `until all the witnesses in attendance have been examined, and if any Special Court finds the adjournment`
  line `of the same beyond the following date to be necessary, it shall record its reasons for doing so.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12602)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Forfeiture of funds or property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12602&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where a person has been convicted of an offence under this`
  line `Act, the Special Court trying such offence may, if it is considered necessary so to do, declare that any`
  line `funds or property seized under section 8 shall stand forfeited to the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12603)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12603&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, an appeal shall lie as a matter of`
  line `right from any judgment, sentence or order, not being an interlocutory order, of a Special Court to the`
  line `High Court both on facts and on law.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the judgment, sentence or order appealed from:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty days`
  line `if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the period of`
  line `thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12604)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Protection of action taken under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12604&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the State Government or any officer or authority of the State Government for anything which is`
  line `in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rules or orders made under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12605)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12605&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where any person is prosecuted of an offence under section 4, the burden of`
  line `proving that he had not committed the offence under the said section shall be on him.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12606)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Obligation of certain persons to report about the commission of offence under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12606&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `All officers of Government are hereby required and empowered to assist the police in the execution of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) All village officers and such other officers as may be specified by the Collector or the District`
  line `Magistrate in relation to any area and the inhabitants of such area shall, if they have reason to believe or`
  line `have the knowledge that sati is about to be, or has been, committed in the area shall forthwith report such`
  line `fact to the nearest police station.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12607)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Person convicted of an offence under section 4 to be disqualified from inheriting certain properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=12607&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `A person convicted of an offence under sub-section (1) of section 4 in relation to the`
  line `commission of sati shall be disqualified from inheriting the property of the person in respect of whom`
  line `such sati has been committed or the property of any other person which he would have been entitled to`
  line `inherit on the death of the person in respect of whom such sati has been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (27933)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=27933&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of Act 43 of 1951].--Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001) s.2`
  line `and the First Schedule(w.e.f.3-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (27934)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=27934&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than`
  line `this Act or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (27935)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=27935&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (27936)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Repeal of existing laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065&sectionId=27936&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00003_198803_1517807326065
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force in any State immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act in that State which provide for the prevention or the glorification of sati shall,`
  line `on such commencement, stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under any law repealed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line `Act, and, in particular, any case taken cognizance of by a Special Court under the provisions of any law`
  line `so repealed and pending before it immediately before the commencement of this Act in that State shall`
  line `continue to be dealt with by that Special Court after such commencement as if such Special Court had`
  line `been constituted under section 9 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
